This fix adds a null check before calling `pdf_set_buffer_writing_system`, which prevents using the buffer if the font failed to load. The original code was attempting to set the writing system even when the font loading failed, which could lead to using an uninitialized or corrupted buffer state. This change ensures we only modify the buffer when we have a valid font object.